<section class="section">
  <h2>Project Overview</h2>

  <p>
    This project documents a fluid mechanical dissection of the Stihl BR 700 leaf blower, treated as a compact
    turbomachinery system in which chemical energy is converted into shaft work and ultimately into airflow
    momentum and pressure rise. The assignment required a hands-on teardown, identification of key flow components,
    and an engineering interpretation of how geometry, losses, and operating conditions influence performance.
  </p>

  <p>
    The dissection video is embedded below and serves as the primary visual record of the teardown process and
    component-level observations.
  </p>

  <div style="margin-top: 1rem;">
    <div style="position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden; border-radius: 10px;">
